      "created_by_ref": "identity--ab072f15-9b87-4ee1-898f-b584d41f29b0",
      "description": "WhatsApp successfully identified and disrupted spear phishing attempts linked to NSO Group, a spyware firm blacklisted by the US government. The company is requesting the court to hold NSO in contempt for violating a permanent injunction that prohibited them from targeting WhatsApp and its users. The attacks involved social engineering attempts to trick users into clicking malicious links, as well as creating test accounts and groups on the platform. WhatsApp emphasizes that spyware represents a national security threat and is supporting the Spyware Accountability Initiative through significant contributions. The company continues to protect users through end-to-end encryption and encourages reporting suspicious activity while maintaining updated applications and devices.",
